<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>TSM ZY Music Suite · Demo Conductor</title>
<style>
:root{
  --bg:#07080d;--panel:#0d1018;--panel2:#111827;--text:#f8fafc;--muted:#9ca3af;
  --gold:#ffd230;--green:#39d98a;--purple:#a855f7;--line:rgba(255,255,255,.1);
  --mono:"Courier New",monospace;--head:Arial Black,Impact,sans-serif;
}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{margin:0;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;overflow:hidden}
.shell{height:100vh;display:grid;grid-template-columns:360px 1fr}
.side{background:#090d16;border-right:1px solid var(--line);padding:20px;overflow:auto}
.stage{position:relative;background:#05070c}
iframe{width:100%;height:100%;border:0;background:white}
.logo{width:42px;height:42px;border-radius:10px;background:var(--gold);color:#050505;display:grid;place-items:center;font-family:var(--head);font-size:20px;margin-bottom:14px}
h1{font-family:var(--head);font-size:28px;line-height:1;margin:0 0 8px}
.sub{color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;margin-bottom:18px}
.step{border:1px solid var(--line);background:rgba(255,255,255,.035);border-radius:14px;padding:14px;margin-bottom:12px;cursor:pointer}
.step.active{border-color:rgba(57,217,138,.65);box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(57,217,138,.12)}
.kicker{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--green);letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase}
.step h3{margin:6px 0;font-size:16px}
.step p{margin:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:12px;line-height:1.45}
.controls{position:fixed;right:18px;bottom:18px;display:flex;gap:10px;z-index:10}
button,.btn{border:1px solid var(--line);background:rgba(255,255,255,.08);color:var(--text);padding:11px 14px;border-radius:999px;font-weight:900;cursor:pointer;text-decoration:none}
button.primary,.btn.primary{background:var(--gold);color:#050505;border-color:var(--gold)}
.scriptBox{margin-top:18px;border:1px solid rgba(168,85,247,.3);background:rgba(168,85,247,.08);border-radius:14px;padding:14px}
.scriptBox h2{font-size:15px;margin:0 0 8px;color:#d8b4fe}
.scriptBox pre{white-space:pre-wrap;color:#e5e7eb;font-size:12px;line-height:1.55;font-family:var(--mono);margin:0}
.actionBox{margin-top:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,210,48,.3);background:rgba(255,210,48,.08);border-radius:14px;padding:14px}
.actionBox b{color:var(--gold)}
.url{font-size:10px;color:var(--muted);word-break:break-all;font-family:var(--mono);margin-top:8px}
.topHint{position:absolute;left:18px;top:18px;z-index:4;background:rgba(0,0,0,.72);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:999px;padding:9px 13px;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--green)}
@media(max-width:900px){.shell{grid-template-columns:1fr}.side{height:48vh}.stage{height:52vh}.controls{position:fixed}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="shell">
  <aside class="side">
    <div class="logo">ZY</div>
    <h1>Music Suite Demo Conductor</h1>
    <div class="sub">Use this page during face-to-face demos. It cycles through the whole suite and gives you exactly what to say and click.</div>

    <div id="steps"></div>

    <div class="scriptBox">
      <h2>Say This</h2>
      <pre id="talk"></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="actionBox">
      <b>Button / Action:</b>
      <div id="action" style="margin-top:6px;color:#e5e7eb;font-size:13px;line-height:1.45"></div>
      <div class="url" id="url"></div>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <main class="stage">
    <div class="topHint" id="hint">Step 1 / 6</div>
    <iframe id="frame" src="/html/music-command/marketing.html?v=conductor"></iframe>
  </main>
</div>

<div class="controls">
  <button onclick="prev()">← Back</button>
  <button class="primary" onclick="next()">Next →</button>
  <a class="btn" id="openNew" target="_blank">Open</a>
</div>

<script>
const params = new URLSearchParams(location.search);
const demoToken = params.get("demo_token") || localStorage.getItem("tsm_music_demo_token") || "";

function withToken(path){
  if(!demoToken) return path;
  const sep = path.includes("?") ? "&" : "?";
  return path + sep + "demo_token=" + encodeURIComponent(demoToken);
}

const deck = [
  {
    title:"Marketing Page",
    label:"Position the product",
    url:"/html/music-command/marketing.html?v=conductor",
    action:"Open with the big idea. Do not demo yet. Make them understand the shift first.",
    talk:`This is the TSM ZY Music Suite.

The core idea is simple:
write once, let it evolve.

Most AI tools generate one answer.
Music does not work like that.

Music is iteration, comparison, taste, and decision-making.

This suite is designed to help artists, producers, and songwriters improve a song until it is actually ready.`
  },
  {
    title:"Protected Live Presentation",
    label:"Create urgency + trust",
    url:withToken("/html/music-command/presentation-live.html?v=conductor"),
    action:"Click Run Cinematic Demo or Run Live Demo. Let the system animate before talking too much.",
    talk:`This is the controlled demo environment.

Every link can be private, expiring, watermarked, and tracked.

That matters because this is not just a public landing page.
It is a controlled sales experience.

Now watch the product engine wake up:
DNA loads, agents activate, and the system runs a live improvement pass.`
  },
  {
    title:"Guided Creation App",
    label:"Show the real product",
    url:"/html/music-command/index.html?v=conductor",
    action:"Click Load Sample & Run. Then point to Hit Score, Pick This, and Improve Picked Version.",
    talk:`Now we are inside the actual app.

This is where the creator works.

They paste a lyric, run the full chain, and the system gives them scored options.

The key is not that it writes lyrics.
The key is that it removes decision friction.

It tells the user:
which version is stronger,
why it is stronger,
and what to do next.`
  },
  {
    title:"Auto-Evolution Loop",
    label:"Make the aha moment clear",
    url:"/html/music-command/index.html?v=loopfix",
    action:"Use the recommended card. Click Improve Picked Version. Show score / trajectory moving.",
    talk:`This is the moment that makes the app feel different.

Instead of restarting from scratch,
the recommended version becomes the next draft.

Then the system improves it again.

Generate.
Improve.
Score.
Repeat.
Stop when it is ready.

That is why this feels like a producer sitting next to you.`
  },
  {
    title:"How-To Guide",
    label:"Show users can learn fast",
    url:"/html/music-command/how-to-guide.html?v=conductor",
    action:"Point to workflow sections. Explain that users do not need to understand AI to use it.",
    talk:`The How-To Guide turns this into a repeatable workflow.

The user does not need to understand AI.
They only need to understand the process:

paste a draft,
run the chain,
pick the strongest version,
improve it,
and track whether the song is getting closer to release-ready.`
  },
  {
    title:"Outreach + Deal Room",
    label:"Close the business case",
    url:"/html/music-command/marketing.html?v=close",
    action:"Explain private links, tracking, urgency, and follow-up. Then ask the qualifier.",
    talk:`The business side is built into the system.

We can create private demo links,
limit views,
watermark each prospect,
track usage,
and follow up based on real activity.

That means we are not just sending a link.
We are creating a controlled sales environment.

The close is simple:
If this helped you finish stronger songs faster,
would it help more with speed, quality, or both?`
  }
];

let i = 0;

function render(){
  document.getElementById("steps").innerHTML = deck.map((s,idx)=>`
    <div class="step ${idx===i?'active':''}" onclick="go(${idx})">
      <div class="kicker">Step ${idx+1}</div>
      <h3>${s.title}</h3>
      <p>${s.label}</p>
    </div>
  `).join("");

  const s = deck[i];
  document.getElementById("frame").src = s.url;
  document.getElementById("talk").textContent = s.talk;
  document.getElementById("action").textContent = s.action;
  document.getElementById("url").textContent = s.url;
  document.getElementById("hint").textContent = `Step ${i+1} / ${deck.length}`;
  document.getElementById("openNew").href = s.url;
}

function go(n){i=n;render()}
function next(){i=(i+1)%deck.length;render()}
function prev(){i=(i-1+deck.length)%deck.length;render()}

document.addEventListener("keydown", e=>{
  if(e.key==="ArrowRight" || e.key==="ArrowDown") next();
  if(e.key==="ArrowLeft" || e.key==="ArrowUp") prev();
});

render();
</script>
</body>
</html>
